         <abstract>
            <p>This record refers to a collection of miracles of the Trinity transmitted together with
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1300Dersan"/>, described in the following paragraphs.
               It is different from <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2281Trinity"/> (a collection of miracles of the Trinity attributed
               to <persName ref="PRS2748BeduaA"/>) and from
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2286ZenaSellase"/> (the collection of prayers to the Trinity
               <ref type="work" corresp="LIT2296Sayfas"/> arranged according
               to the days of the week with miracles of the Trinity).</p>
            <p>
               From     <bibl>
                  <ptr target="bm:Nosnitsin2010EAETammeraS"/>
               </bibl> (minimally rephrased):
            This set of miracles is part of the <ref type="work" corresp="LIT1300Dersan">Dǝrsāna Śǝllāse</ref>. The miracles mostly conform to the pattern of
            <foreign xml:lang="gez">taʾammǝr</foreign>, telling of wonders worked by the Trinity both abroad (Egypt, Palestine etc., occasionally
            picking biblical stories) and in Ethiopia.</p>
            <p>This work is attested in <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML150"/>, <ref type="mss" corresp="EMML1882"/>
               and <ref type="mss" corresp="SHOr409"/>.</p>
         </abstract>
